Remittances of Egyptians Abroad Rise to $2.9 Billion in January 2025

### English Text Summary:
Remittances from Egyptians working abroad increased to $2.9 billion in January 2025, marking the highest flow for this month since records began, according to the Central Bank of Egypt. The rise is attributed to the stability of the Egyptian pound against the dollar and attractive high-yield savings instruments. Since the floatation of the pound in March 2024, remittances have surged to $20 billion in the first seven months of the fiscal year 2024/2025, up 81% from the previous year. Experts predict continued growth in remittances, unaffected by fluctuations in the pound's exchange rate, supported by expected Gulf investments and the economic stability of the region.

